古埃及人也用荷魯斯之眼來計數。古埃及人將荷魯斯之眼拆解為6個部份，每個部份各代表著一個[[分數|分數]]，構成一個[[等比級數|等比級數]]，相加起來便是一個荷魯斯之眼，代表著[[1|1]]。<ref>Zaslavsky, Claudia (1993). ''Multicultural Mathematics: Interdisciplinary Cooperative-Learning Activities'', p.20. ISBN 9780825121814.</ref><ref>{{cite book | title=Professor Stewart's Hoard of Mathematical Treasures | url=https://archive.org/details/professorstewart0000stew_i8r6 | last=Stewart | first=Ian | publisher=Profile Books | ISBN=978 1 84668 292 6 | year= 2009 | pages=[https://archive.org/details/professorstewart0000stew_i8r6/page/76 76]–80 }}</ref>
具體而言即：
:等式A：<math>\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{4}+\frac{1}{8}+\frac{1}{16}+\frac{1}{32}+\frac{1}{64}+\cdots = \sum_{n=1}^\infty \left({\frac 12}\right)^n =1</math>

:等式B：<math>\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{4}+\frac{1}{8}+\frac{1}{16}+\frac{1}{32}+\frac{1}{64}+\frac{1}{64} =1</math>
事實上，無窮等比級數「等式A」右邊尚差<math>\frac{1}{64}</math>（其和等於「等式B」），但古埃及人將其捨去。有七個不同的象形文字代表的眼球，最常用[[圣书体|圣书体]]「{{lang|al|ir.t}}」表示<ref name="Henadology">{{cite web |url=http://henadology.wordpress.com/theology/netjeru/wadjet |title=Wadjet |author=Butler, Edward P |date= |work=Goddesses and Gods of the Ancient Egyptians: A Theological Encyclopedia |publisher=Henadology: Philosophy and Theology |accessdate=October 4, 2010 |archive-date=2016-04-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401191555/https://henadology.wordpress.com/theology/netjeru/wadjet/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。
